description.narrative: UNICEF continued providing support to the National Council for Family Affairs (NCFA) and key stakeholders to duly submit the childhood and juvenile laws to the cabinet for endorsement. If passed, the laws will allow children in Jordan to more fully enjoy their rights by eliminating some key gaps in the current legislations. UNICEF also supported knowledge and evidence on issues related to child protection to be generated, such as the costing study of the draft Childhood Law and the national violence against children study. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/08/2020
